ntcRS.description: This MIB Module defines the Rate Shaping MIB. More detailed description of the variables and tables is provided in other related documentation.

PacketSource.name: PacketSource
PacketSource.description: The source of the packet rate-limited for. input statistics of the input packets. output statistics of the output packets.

RateLimitAction.name: RateLimitAction
RateLimitAction.description: The action taken after evaluating the rate limit. drop drop the packet. accept transmit the packet. reject discard the packet and return ICMP error message. condition pass to the traffic conditioner. skip inactive rule, must perform default action. prioritize prioritize the packet.

rsAccessLists.name: rsAccessLists
rsAccessLists.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsAccessLists

rsAccessListTable.name: rsAccessListTable
rsAccessListTable.description: A table of access list configuration entries. An access list will contain several rules for rate limits which are applied to one or more MIB-II interface-direction tuples. Each MIB-II interface may not utilize more than two access lists; one for the in direction and one for the out direction.

rsAccessListEntry.name: rsAccessListEntry
rsAccessListEntry.description: A series of objects used to describe each access list.

rsAccessListIfIndex.name: rsAccessListIfIndex
rsAccessListIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MIB-II interface which this access list entry is responsible for.

rsAccessListIndex.name: rsAccessListIndex
rsAccessListIndex.description: A unique index value for this access list.

rsAccessListDirection.name: rsAccessListDirection
rsAccessListDirection.description: The data source for this access list.

rsAccessListName.name: rsAccessListName
rsAccessListName.description: This string provides a unique descriptor for this access list. If an attempt is made to set this string to the name of another access list on the agent, it should return noSuchName.

rsAccessListRowStatus.name: rsAccessListRowStatus
rsAccessListRowStatus.description: The current status of this access list. Setting this object to 'destroy' has the effect of deleting this access list. createAndGo(4) appends to the list and activates it.

rsRules.name: rsRules
rsRules.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsRules

rsRuleTable.name: rsRuleTable
rsRuleTable.description: A table of rate limit configuration entries. Rate Limit is a method of traffic control. It allows a set of rate limits to be configured and applied to packets flowing into/out of an interface to regulate network traffic.

rsRuleEntry.name: rsRuleEntry
rsRuleEntry.description: A collection of rate-limit configuration objects on this interface. Entries in the rsRuleTable is created and deleted via the rate-limit command line interface.

rsRuleIfIndex.name: rsRuleIfIndex
rsRuleIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MIB-II interface which this access list entry is responsible for.

rsRuleIndex.name: rsRuleIndex
rsRuleIndex.description: An arbitrary index for rate limit objects. It will increase as the list for each rsRuleIfIndex is traversed.In other words,the value of rsRuleIndex increments for the same value of rsRuleIfIndex, but starts over at 1 once the value of rsRuleIfIndex changes.

rsRuleDirection.name: rsRuleDirection
rsRuleDirection.description: The data source for the Rate Limit object.

rsRuleTOS.name: rsRuleTOS
rsRuleTOS.description: The TOS field of the type of packet which this rule governs.

rsRuleAction.name: rsRuleAction
rsRuleAction.description: The forwarding Action associated with this rule.

rsRuleSrcAddress.name: rsRuleSrcAddress
rsRuleSrcAddress.description: The source IP address for this rule.

rsRuleSrcAddrMask.name: rsRuleSrcAddrMask
rsRuleSrcAddrMask.description: The mask of source address for this rule.

rsRuleDestAddress.name: rsRuleDestAddress
rsRuleDestAddress.description: The destination IP address for this rule.

rsRuleDestAddrMask.name: rsRuleDestAddrMask
rsRuleDestAddrMask.description: The mask of destination address for this rule.

rsRuleIpProtocol.name: rsRuleIpProtocol
rsRuleIpProtocol.description: The number of IP protocol that rule applies on.

rsRuleSrcStartingPort.name: rsRuleSrcStartingPort
rsRuleSrcStartingPort.description: The start of the source range of port number(s) of the IP protocol for this rule.

rsRuleSrcEndingPort.name: rsRuleSrcEndingPort
rsRuleSrcEndingPort.description: The end of the source range of port number(s) of the IP protocol for this rule.

rsRuleDestStartingPort.name: rsRuleDestStartingPort
rsRuleDestStartingPort.description: The start of the destination range of port number(s) of the IP protocol for this rule.

rsRuleDestEndingPort.name: rsRuleDestEndingPort
rsRuleDestEndingPort.description: The end of the destination range of port number(s) of the IP protocol for this rule.

rsRuleAggregationClassIndex.name: rsRuleAggregationClassIndex
rsRuleAggregationClassIndex.description: The index(rsAggregationClassIndex) to the aggregation class(queue) if RateLimitAction is enqueue(3).

rsRuleEstablished.name: rsRuleEstablished
rsRuleEstablished.description: An integer value indicating whether or not this rule is effective on previously-established TCP connections. 'established' will indicate that upon activation of this rule, only previously-established TCP connections will match this rule. 'notEstablished' will indicate that any TCP connection can match this rule.

rsRuleRowStatus.name: rsRuleRowStatus
rsRuleRowStatus.description: The current status of this rule. The rules defined in this table is treated as a linked list. By definition rsRuleRowStatus will ensure that there are no orphan rules i.e the linked list is not broken. Setting a rule to 'destroy' has the effect of deleting this rule. createAndGo(4) appends to the list thus ensuring that there are no orphans.

rsAggregationClasses.name: rsAggregationClasses
rsAggregationClasses.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsAggregationClasses

rsAggregationClassTable.name: rsAggregationClassTable
rsAggregationClassTable.description: A table of aggregation class entries.

rsAggregationClassEntry.name: rsAggregationClassEntry
rsAggregationClassEntry.description: A collection of aggregation class objects on this interface-direction tuple.

rsAggregationClassIfIndex.name: rsAggregationClassIfIndex
rsAggregationClassIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex which corresponds to the first interface for which this aggregation class handles tokens.

rsAggregationClassIndex.name: rsAggregationClassIndex
rsAggregationClassIndex.description: The unique row index of this aggregation class(queue).

rsAggregationClassDirection.name: rsAggregationClassDirection
rsAggregationClassDirection.description: The data source for this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassName.name: rsAggregationClassName
rsAggregationClassName.description: A string which uniquely represents this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassMeanRate.name: rsAggregationClassMeanRate
rsAggregationClassMeanRate.description: The peak bandwidth when rsAggregationClassBurstRate and rsAggregationClassBurstDuration are not set. When mean rate and burst duration are set, the mean rate specifies the long-term rate which the packet stream will be shaped to, but the packet stream can burst above that rate for as long as the burst duration specifies with no penalty. The value noSuchName should be returned if an attempt is made to set the value to a rate is higher than the rate available to this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassBurstSize.name: rsAggregationClassBurstSize
rsAggregationClassBurstSize.description: The Burst size associated with this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassRowStatus.name: rsAggregationClassRowStatus
rsAggregationClassRowStatus.description: The current status of this aggregation class. The behavior of this aggregation class upon changing of this object should be analogous to the behavior of a rule when its rsRuleRowStatus is modified.

rsAccessListStats.name: rsAccessListStats
rsAccessListStats.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsAccessListStats

rsAccessListStatTable.name: rsAccessListStatTable
rsAccessListStatTable.description: A table of access list status entries.

rsAccessListStatEntry.name: rsAccessListStatEntry
rsAccessListStatEntry.description: A series of status objects used to describe each access list.

rsAccessListStatIfIndex.name: rsAccessListStatIfIndex
rsAccessListStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MIB-II interface which this access list stat entry is responsible for.

rsAccessListStatIndex.name: rsAccessListStatIndex
rsAccessListStatIndex.description: A unique index value for this access list.

rsAccessListStatDirection.name: rsAccessListStatDirection
rsAccessListStatDirection.description: The data source for this access list.

rsAccessListStatPktsPassed.name: rsAccessListStatPktsPassed
rsAccessListStatPktsPassed.description: Gives the count of number of packets successfully exiting this access list.

rsAccessListStatBytesPassed.name: rsAccessListStatBytesPassed
rsAccessListStatBytesPassed.description: Gives the count of number of bytes successfully exiting this access list.

rsRuleStats.name: rsRuleStats
rsRuleStats.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsRuleStats

rsRuleStatTable.name: rsRuleStatTable
rsRuleStatTable.description: A table of rate limit status entries.

rsRuleStatEntry.name: rsRuleStatEntry
rsRuleStatEntry.description: A collection of rate-limit status objects on this interface.

rsRuleStatIfIndex.name: rsRuleStatIfIndex
rsRuleStatIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex which corresponds to the interface for which this rule is applied to.

rsRuleStatIndex.name: rsRuleStatIndex
rsRuleStatIndex.description: The rsRuleIndex value of the rule this entry describes.

rsRuleStatDirection.name: rsRuleStatDirection
rsRuleStatDirection.description: The data source for this rule.

rsRuleStatDropPkts.name: rsRuleStatDropPkts
rsRuleStatDropPkts.description: The counter of packets which exceeded this rate limit.

rsRuleStatDropOctets.name: rsRuleStatDropOctets
rsRuleStatDropOctets.description: The counter of bytes which exceeded this rate limit.

rsRuleStatPktsPassed.name: rsRuleStatPktsPassed
rsRuleStatPktsPassed.description: Gives the count of number of packets successfully exiting this rule.

rsRuleStatBytesPassed.name: rsRuleStatBytesPassed
rsRuleStatBytesPassed.description: Gives the count of number of bytes successfully exiting this rule.

rsAggregationClassStats.name: rsAggregationClassStats
rsAggregationClassStats.description: A collection of objects providing the instrumentation of rsAggregationClassStats

rsAggregationClassStatTable.name: rsAggregationClassStatTable
rsAggregationClassStatTable.description: A table of aggregation class status entries.

rsAggregationClassStatEntry.name: rsAggregationClassStatEntry
rsAggregationClassStatEntry.description: A collection of aggregation class status objects on this interface. Entries are created and deleted via the rate-limit command line interface.

rsAggregationClassStatIfIndex.name: rsAggregationClassStatIfIndex
rsAggregationClassStatIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex which corresponds to the interface for which this aggregation class handles tokens for.

rsAggregationClassStatIndex.name: rsAggregationClassStatIndex
rsAggregationClassStatIndex.description: The value of rsAggregationClassIndex for the aggregation class which this entry describes.

rsAggregationClassStatDirection.name: rsAggregationClassStatDirection
rsAggregationClassStatDirection.description: The data source for this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassStatShapedPkts.name: rsAggregationClassStatShapedPkts
rsAggregationClassStatShapedPkts.description: The counter of packets shaped by this rate limit.

rsAggregationClassStatShapedOctets.name: rsAggregationClassStatShapedOctets
rsAggregationClassStatShapedOctets.description: The counter of bytes shaped by this interface.

rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedPkts.name: rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedPkts
rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedPkts.description: The counter of packets enqueued by this rate limit.

rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedOctets.name: rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedOctets
rsAggregationClassStatEnqueuedOctets.description: The counter of enqueued bytes by this rate limit.

rsAggregationClassStatDroppedPkts.name: rsAggregationClassStatDroppedPkts
rsAggregationClassStatDroppedPkts.description: The counter of packets which exceeded this rate limit.

rsAggregationClassStatDroppedOctets.name: rsAggregationClassStatDroppedOctets
rsAggregationClassStatDroppedOctets.description: The counter of bytes which exceeded this rate limit.

rsAggregationClassStatInputPktsPassed.name: rsAggregationClassStatInputPktsPassed
rsAggregationClassStatInputPktsPassed.description: The counter of packets successfully exiting this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassStatOutputPktsPassed.name: rsAggregationClassStatOutputPktsPassed
rsAggregationClassStatOutputPktsPassed.description: The counter of packets successfully exiting this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassStatInputBytesPassed.name: rsAggregationClassStatInputBytesPassed
rsAggregationClassStatInputBytesPassed.description: The counter of bytes successfully exiting this aggregation class.

rsAggregationClassStatOutputBytesPassed.name: rsAggregationClassStatOutputBytesPassed
rsAggregationClassStatOutputBytesPassed.description: The counter of bytes successfully exiting this aggregation class.
